text:
A giant swarm of flying ants registered on the weather radar above England.

“During the summer ants can take to the skies in a mass emergence usually on warm, humid and windless days,” the Met Office, Britain’s national weather service, explained.

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Amsterdam has asked visitors to steer clear of its Red Light District over crowding concerns.

Sex workers legally resumed work on July 1 as the worst of the Netherlands’ COVID-19 outbreak faded, but authorities expressed the floodgates opened too far.
https://t.co/llWE98Vsha

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Domingo German switched stance, saying he has no plans to retire, after posting a cryptic message suggesting he was retiring from baseball.

German is currently serving an 81-game suspension related to a domestic violence incident last year.
https://t.co/qjY3ZAAUHc

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Atlanta Braves star Freddie Freeman said his severe case of coronavirus left him praying for his life.

“I’ve never been that hot before. My body was really, really hot,” Freeman said. “So I said ‘Please don’t take me’ — I wasn’t ready.”
